The bible verse in the book of 1st Corinthians 13:13 aptly describes the bedrock of the nuptial union of Ondo State Governor Rotimi Akeredolu and his wife, Betty. The couple have continued to apply the teachings of the verse from the beginning of their union till their 41st wedding anniversary as husband and wife. The celebration of their 41st wedding anniversary revealed the hidden side of Akeredolu as the two love birds engaged in a Public Display of Affection on social media. Responding to his wife’s reassurance of their enduring love tale, Akeredolu responded by expressing his rekindled and undying love for the woman he described as his ‘Adaowere.’ 		 			Adekunle Olayinka is battle ready		 		 		 			Kola-Balogun Smith’s political move		 		 		 			The Spirit of Africa at 69		 		 Governor Akeredolu who was on a medical break abroad, returned to the country to celebrate with his family. During the occasion of their wedding anniversary, Akeredolu also threw his weight behind his wife who is seeking an elective post to Imo state House of Assembly come 2023. According to the Ondo Governor, Mrs. Betty has contested for the House of Representatives before he ever thought of delving into active politics. Society Rendezvous gathered that the duo had a quiet private celebration, where close friends and family members were privileged to attend and share in their joy.